Class Deque<Item>

  • java.lang.Object
    • Deque<Item>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Item>

    public class Deque<Item>
extends Object
implements Iterable<Item>
    The Deque class is a generic data type that supports adding and removing items from either the front or the back of the data structure as defined at Programming Assignment 2: Deques and Randomized Queues
    Author:
    Ashutosh Grewal
